        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 22 at 4:25PM CDT by NWS Aberdeen SD</headline>
        <description>At 425 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Thunderbird Colony, or 15 miles northwest of Faulkton, moving east at
25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Brentwood Colony, Cresbard, Thunderbird Colony, Norbeck, Blumengard
Colony, and Loyalton.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
